text.tspan: Death rates from outdoor air pollution in 1990 vs. 2017
Death rates from outdoor air pollution are measured as the number of deaths per 100,000 individuals.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
Note: To allow comparisons between countries and over time this metric is age-standardized.
